{
  "text": "For the case of general demands, no constant approximation was known. The best known approximation due to Andrews et al. [CITATION_1] was O (k + log q\u22121 \u0394), where k = |D| is the number of demands and \u0394 = max i d i is the size of the largest demand (Theorem 8 in Andrews et al. [CITATION_2] ).",
